President Barack Obama issued a proclamation declaring September 20-26, 2009, as National Farm Safety and Health Week. In the proclamation, he acknowledges the significant risks faced by farmers and ranchers in their everyday duties, such as operating heavy and hazardous equipment and working in extreme weather conditions. He also highlights the potential health risks associated with exposure to pesticides, fertilizers, chemicals, and dust. The President encourages farm and ranch families and workers to participate in farm safety and health programs and follow optimal safety practices. He emphasizes the importance of preventing accidents, exposure to hazards, and saving lives. President Obama expresses gratitude for the contributions of farmers and ranchers to the nation and calls for continued commitment to safety and health standards in the agricultural sector.